## MCP

`mcp.json` configures remote MCP servers for AI agents. Currently includes Linear.

### Linear MCP

- **URL**: `https://mcp.linear.app/mcp`
- **Auth**: OAuth (browser-based on first use)
- **Scope**: Issues, projects, teams, documents in the AiluraCode workspace

### Usage

- Create issues via the Linear MCP server tools.
- Search and update issues in the AiluraCode workspace.
- Authenticate on first use (OAuth in browser).

### This repository → Linear mapping

Issues for **this repo** (`alpinejs-toolkit`) MUST always be created with:

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| `team` | `Alpine` |
| `project` | `Alpine Toolkit` |
| Repo link | `https://github.com/ailuracode/alpinejs-toolkit` |

`mcp.json` only configures the MCP connection — it cannot set a default project. Agents MUST pass `project` explicitly on every `save_issue` call.

Example:

```ts
save_issue({
  team: "Alpine",
  project: "Alpine Toolkit",
  title: "Short issue title",
  description: "## Summary\n\n…",
});
```

Branch names for issue-driven work follow `.cursor/rules/branches.mdc` (`<coder>/alp-<n>-<description>`).

### Rules

- Never put Linear issue identifiers in commit messages — link from PR description only.
- PR title uses conventional commits, not Linear identifiers.
- One issue per PR.
